        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10609.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. C. Marshall, 19 September 1876</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had asked Marshall, an architect, to undertake the building of a billiard room onto Down House, with a bedroom and dressing-room above (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10609.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. C. Marshall, 19 September 1876</ref>). <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7905.xml">Isaac Withers Laslett</ref> was a local builder. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8080.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Alfred Deards</ref> was a builder based in London.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref> was CD’s youngest son.</note>
